leading-[1.7]">Here's a breakdown of all 16 tables and how the four actor r=
oles connect:</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>The four actors and their profile tables</strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">All actors share a single <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border borde=
r-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem=
] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">users</code> table with a <code class=3D"bg-tex=
t-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-=
wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">role</code> enum (<code cla=
ss=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whi=
tespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">super_admin</co=
de>, <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-=
danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">p=
ublisher</code>, <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-bord=
er-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text=
-[0.9rem]">author</code>, <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 bo=
rder-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 p=
y-px text-[0.9rem]">reader</code>). Each role then extends into its own pro=
file table linked via <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border=
-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px=
 text-[0.9rem]">user_id</code>, keeping authentication unified while storin=
g role-specific data separately.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Super Admin</strong> =E2=80=94 manages the platform through=
 <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-dang=
er-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">super=
_admin</code> (with a <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border=
-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px=
 text-[0.9rem]">permissions</code> JSON field), handles <code class=3D"bg-t=
ext-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pr=
e-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">reports</code> (reviewing=
 flagged content/users), moderates <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border bord=
er-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4re=
m] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">reviews</code>, verifies publishers, and sends=
 <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-dang=
er-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">notif=
ications</code>.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Publisher</strong> =E2=80=94 owns the content pipeline: cre=
ates <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-=
danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">c=
omic_series</code>, gets assigned <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border borde=
r-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem=
] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">authors</code>, and controls publication status=
. Publishers are verified by Super Admin before going live.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Author</strong> =E2=80=94 belongs to a publisher and writes=
 individual <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-30=
0 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9=
rem]">issues</code>. This is the fourth actor =E2=80=94 separating authorsh=
ip from publishing is important since one publisher can have many writers, =
and credit needs to be tracked per issue.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Reader</strong> =E2=80=94 the consumer side. Readers have a=
 <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-dang=
er-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">subsc=
ription_tier</code> (free/premium), track <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 bord=
er border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded=
-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">reading_progress</code> per issue and p=
age, <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-=
danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">b=
ookmark</code> series, write <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5=
 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-=
1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">reviews</code>, and can file <code class=3D"bg-text-=
200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wr=
ap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">reports</code>.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><strong>Key design decisions</strong></p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]">The <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-30=
0 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9=
rem]">pages</code> table stores each comic page as a separate row with <cod=
e class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-00=
0 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">image_url<=
/code> and <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300=
 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9r=
em]">thumbnail_url</code>, which allows lazy loading and granular reading p=
rogress tracking via <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-=
border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px =
text-[0.9rem]">last_page_read</code> in <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border=
 border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[=
0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">reading_progress</code>.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 te=
xt-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]=
">is_premium</code> exists on both <code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border bord=
er-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4re=
m] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">comic_series</code> and <code class=3D"bg-text=
-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-w=
rap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">issues</code> =E2=80=94 some=
 series are free overall but have premium issues (e.g. bonus content), so t=
he flag at both levels gives publishers flexibility.</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 te=
xt-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]=
">series_tags</code> is a junction table allowing many-to-many tagging (a s=
eries can be "Action", "Sci-Fi", and "Mature" simultaneously).</p>
<p class=3D"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading=
-[1.7]"><code class=3D"bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 te=
xt-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]=
